  "description": "The dish uses South Indian evening-tiffin logic: quick-cooking grains, legumes, and aromatic tempering for depth without richness. Oats and Red Rice Idli with Sambar brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Steam the idlis on medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes until springy and fully set.",
    "For the saaru, simmer dal, tomato, vegetable, garlic, cumin, pepper, salt, and 400 ml water over medium heat for 10 minutes until fragrant and lightly broth-like.",
    "Temper with a little oil if desired and pour the hot saaru into bowls.",
    "Serve the idlis alongside or submerged briefly so they soak up the broth."
  ],
